POLICE are trying to trace three men after a man was found dead in an Edinburgh street. Police hunt suspects as man found dead in street POLICE are trying to trace three men after a man was found dead in an Edinburgh street.The 46-year-old was found at Restalrig Circus after officers were called to a disturbance in the early hours of Saturday morning.The man was taken to Edinburgh Royal Infirmary but was later pronounced dead.The death is being treated by police as murder.Police Scotland are keen to trace three men seen in the area at the time.Detective Chief Inspector Keith Hardie added: &quot;We believe the victim had been in the Tor public house prior to the murder.&quot; 